1 A BILL for an Act to create and enact chapter 27-20.5 of the North Dakota Century Code,
2 relating to fitness to proceed and remediation of juveniles; to amend and reenact section
3 12.1-04-01, subsections 4 and 5 of section 12.1-04-08, subsection 5 of section 27-20.3-01, and
4 section 27-20.4-15 of the North Dakota Century Code, relating to the age of an offender,
5 suspension or dismissal of proceedings, predispositional assessment, and the definition of a
6 child in need of protection; to provide an appropriation; and to provide an effective date.
7 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
8 SECTION 1. AMENDMENT. Section 12.1-04-01 of the North Dakota Century Code is
9 amended and reenacted as follows:
10 12.1-04-01. Juveniles.
11 1. An individual under the age of ten years is deemed incapable of commission of an
12 offense defined by the constitution or statutes of this state. The prosecution of an individual as
13 an adult is barred if the offense was committed while the individual was less than fourteen years
14 of age.
15 2. An individual ten years of age or older may be assessed for mental fitness or capacity
16 under this chapter.
17 SECTION 2. AMENDMENT. Subsection 4 of section 12.1-04-08 of the North Dakota
18 Century Code is amended and reenacted as follows:
19 4. If the court determines the defendant currently lacks fitness to proceed and the
20 defendant may attain fitness to proceed under subsection 12, the court may enter an
21 order for a course of treatment considering the least restrictive form of treatment
22 therapeutically appropriate.
