1 raised by the court before which the proceedings are pending or being held, or by
2 motion of a party, at any time during the proceeding.
3 2. If the minor's fitness to proceed is raised, adjudication may not occur until after a
4 determination is made on the fitness of the minor to proceed in accordance with this
5 chapter.
6 27 - 20.5 - 04. Use of previous findings and records - Deflection .
7 A minor who is found to lack fitness to proceed due to previous judicial findings of lack of
8 fitness to proceed or considerations from school, medical, or other records within the last twelve
9 months may have the delinquency proceedings dismissed before a fitness to proceed
10 examination or remediation services are administered.
11 27 - 20.5 - 05. Due process .
12 1. If the minor's fitness to proceed is raised, adjudication may not occur until after a
13 determination is made except the filing of a delinquency petition, until counsel is
14 appointed and notified in accordance with section 27 - 20.2 - 12 and the minor is found to
15 have the mental capacity to proceed.
16 2. After the case proceeds to adjudication or the minor is found to lack fitness to proceed,
17 the court shall order all of the reports that are submitted under this chapter to be
18 closed to the public. The court may order the reports be opened for inspection only:
19 a. For further fitness to proceed or criminal responsibility examination;
20 b. For statistical analysis;
21 c. If the records are considered to be necessary to assist in mental health treatment
22 ordered according to the mental health code;
23 d. For data gathering;
24 e. For scientific study or other legitimate research;
25 f. To the state's attorney or minor's counsel for the purpose of an active court case
26 subject to the prior evaluation; and
27 g. To an employee or agent of the division of juvenile services or the department of
28 health and human services, if necessary in the performance of the employee's or
29 agent's duty.
30 3. If the court orders a report to be open for the purpose of de-identified statistical
31 analysis, data gathering, or scientific study, the report must remain confidential.
